captions.text:
Hi, I'm William Shatner
and I love fried turkey.

But turkey and oil are
a dangerous combination.
So watch this video.
I want your comments on it.

I want to know how you plan
to keep yourself, your family,

and me safe from
turkey fryer fire.

(SINGING) I want a
deep fried turkey.

I want a moister,
tastier, turkey.
I want a deep fried turkey.

I want a moister,
tastier turkey.
It started as a hunger.

I was young and arrogant,
(I was young and arrogant.)

Blinded by my hunger
I ignored safety.
I want a deep fried turkey.

I want a moister,
tastier turkey.
I want a deep fried turkey.

I want a moister,
tastier turkey.

When I laid my
hands on that fryer

I didn't want to
let go (let go).

Back then everyone was doing
it. (Everyone was doing it.)
I once love this piece of metal.

Keep yourself, your family,
and me safe from turkey fryer
fires.

So dangerous, you
can't even imagine.

Fried turkey tastes
great, great taste.
I love fried turkey.
But you got to be safe.

Pot, (pot) thermometer,
(thermometer) dingle dangle,
dingle dangle.

Pot, (pot), thermometer,
where's the dingle dangle?

Hot oil with frozen
turkey pushed together

makes steam, pushing the hot oil
and igniting on the open flame.
I want a deep fried turkey.

I want a moister,
tastier, turkey.
I want a deep fried turkey.

I want a moister,
tastier turkey.

Blinded by my hunger I ignored
safety. (I ignored safety.)
Spat in the face of science.

Turn off the flame,
turn off the flame.
Oh, my goodness!
What have I done?
Oh, ow!
Oh, look at this!
That is so stupid!

Keep yourself, your family, and
me safe from turkey fryer fire.

So dangerous, you
can't even imagine.
I want a deep fried turkey.

I want a moister,
tastier turkey.
I want a deep fried turkey.

I want a moister,
tastier turkey.

That fryer took so much from me,
but it gave me a healthy fear.

Fire, metal, oil, and turkey
are glorious when in harmony,

but their power is
unrelenting in careless hands.

title: State Farm® - Eat, Fry, Love: A Cautionary Remix

comments.text:
How I kept myself safe from accidents involving a turkey fryer...

I roasted my turkey in an oven instead.

But, there are safety tips to follow when frying turkeys.  For instance, 
the bird must be thoroughly thawed and the skin must be patted dry.  And, 
when lowering the bird into the pot, turn the gas off.  Once the bird is 
safely in, reignite the burner.

And, don't overestimate how much oil you need; it's very easy to add too 
much oil and have the turkey displace the excess out of the pot.﻿
